                             ARCHIVER
                                by
                             Mike Ford

     With Easy Arc, you can create, view or extract archives in all
 the popular Amiga formats (Arc, Pak, Lharc, Zoo, Warp and LHWarp).
     Simple point and click execution. You supply the destination
 directories in fields provided.


I. Requirements  
     The Following Files located in C:directory of boot disk
          
          ***********absolute requirements************** 

        Deckbrowser (if deckbrowser is moved from the C directory
                     change the default tool for miniarc to reflect
                     where it is located with the INFO Worbench menu.)
        Assign
        Delete
        Failat
        Endcli
        Ask
        Endcli
        NewCli
    
   C: directory (boot disk - required only if you want these to work.)
       Arc
       Lharc
       Zoo
       Pak
       LHwarp
       Warp


II. The Main Screen. (buttons)
   A. ARC  ---- create or add files in the Arc format        (.arc)
   B. LHARC --- create or add files in the Lharc format      (.lzh)
   C. ZOO  ---- create or add files in the Zoo format        (.zoo)
   D. PAK  ---- create or add files in the PAK format        (.pak)
   E. WARP ---- compress an entire disk in the Warp format   (.wrp)
   F. LHWARP -- compress an entire disk in the Lhwarp format (.lhw) 
   G. EXTRACT FILES - Extract Archived Files
   H. LIST FILES    - Lists Archived Files
   I. QUIT     - Quits the program

   To create an archive, click either the Arc, Lharc, Zoo, Pak, Lhwarp
      or Warp button.

   To List the files in an archive click List Files.

   To Extract the files of any archive type click  Extract Files

III. FileSelect Screen Windows
 |---------------------| |---------------------|   |----------------------|
 |                     | |                     |   |                      |
 |(Volumes/Directories)| |      (Files)        |   |      (Action)        |
 |                     | |                     |   |                      |
 |---------------------| |                     |   |                      |
                         |---------------------|   |----------------------|

   A. Action Files Document - contains a list of files to be acted on.
      To Remove a file from this document. Double click the name.
   B. Volumes/Directories  - contains a list of available disk volumes or
      directories. Double click the line to see the available files.
   C. Files Document - contains a list of files in the current directory.
      To move a file from here to the Action Files Doc, double click it.


IV. File Select Screen Buttons and Fields
   A. Path Field - displays the current directory. You may type in this
      field and hit return if you dont wan't to use the documents.
   B. Destination Field - The destination path of the Archive or Extract
      Command.
   C. Command Field - The default command for the action you selected.
   D. Go Button- executes the command in the command field.
   E. Exit Button - returns to Main Screen.
   H. NewCli - Opens a newshell or newcli
   I. Disk Button - Displays the available volumes
   J. Parent Button - Moves Current Directory up one in Path
   M. Clear Button - Clears the Action Document
   
   To CREATE a new archive or add files to existing archives, Double
     Click the line in the Files document and move it to the Action
     Document. Double Click as many as you want. When satisfied. Click
     The Go Button.

   To LIST or EXTRACT an Archive double click the file you want in the files
     document to move it to the Action Document. If you select more than one
     the first one will be replaced by the new one. You can only List or
     Extract one file at a time.

   If NoWay !!! appears in the Command field, then that file cannot be
     listed or extracted.

   If you get an error "Command Line Too Long" when creating an archive,
     read the highest arcrunner.num and remove files from the Action
     Document. Your command line can only be 3 lines long. Then repeat
     the process with the files you removed and add them to the archive.

   You may also use the Command field to Test or Print archives by typing
     in the command you wish. You may also want to use the -x0 or -x option
     in LHARC. If so type it in. Update or freshen may not work here.


V. Warp Screen
   Select either GO to Warp or Exit to Abort.
   If Warping enter the Destination Directory and File Name Where you
   want the warped file Stored.


VI. LHWARP Screen
   1. Lhwarping a Disk to a file.
    A. Use the < and > buttons to select the Starting and Ending Tracks or
        Click on the number and type it in.
    B. Click the Drive Button to Cycle between DF0-DF1:
    C. Click The Option Button you want -M,-C,ect. to set the option
       in the option in the option field. Or you may type in the option
       or options you desire.
    D. The Default Option is Freeze Mode which is no option selected
        or a blank option field.
    E. Set the Destination Directory and File Name where you
       want the archive stored.
    F. Select GO  to LHWARP or select EXIT to Abort.
   
  2. If extracting a file compressed by Lhwarp, select the destination
     drive with the drive button. Click Go to continue or Exit to abort.
